Standardized processing of raw data
The definitions and measurement units of the evaluation indicators in the evaluation system for the capability of special economic zones to carry out the green transformation of industries are different, thus it is necessary to classify the above indicators into two categories for dimensionless processing in order to facilitate a unified comparison. The positive indicators undergo standardized processing according to the following processing method:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ x_{ij}^{'} = \frac{{x_{ij} - \hbox{min} x_{ij} }}{{\hbox{max} x_{ij} - \hbox{min} x_{ij} }}\quad (0 \le x_{ij}^{'} \le 1) $$\end{document}

The negative indicators undergo standardized processing according to the following processing method:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ x_{ij}^{'} = \frac{{\hbox{max} x_{ij} - x_{ij} }}{{\hbox{max} x_{ij} - \hbox{min} x_{ij} }}\quad (0 \le x_{ij}^{'} \le 1) $$\end{document}

2.
Calculation of the entropy, difference coefficient and weight
First, determine the proportions of the indicator values of the evaluation units under each indicator; the calculation formula is shown below:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ p_{ij} = \frac{{x_{ij}^{'} }}{{\sum\limits_{i = 1}^{n} {x_{ij}^{'} } }} $$\end{document}

And then calculate the entropy of each indicator:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ e_{j} = - k\sum\limits_{i = 1}^{n} {p_{ij} } \ln p_{ij} ,\;{\text{where}}\;k = \frac{1}{\ln n}. $$\end{document}

Define the difference coefficient: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ g_{j} = 1 - e_{j} $$\end{document}, calculate the weight according to the difference coefficient:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ a_{j} = \frac{{g_{j} }}{{\sum\limits_{i = 1}^{m} {g_{j} } }} $$\end{document}

3.
Evaluation results
Calculate the comprehensive evaluation value according to the entropy, difference coefficient and weight:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ v_{i} = \sum\limits_{j = 1}^{n} {a_{j} } p_{ij} $$\end{document}
